## **Power Budget Summary**

| Category | Value | Status |
|---|---|---|
| **Per-pin load** | ≤20 mA | ✅ Safe |
| **Total board draw** | ~35 mA (7 LEDs @ 5mA + digital I/O) | ✅ Well within 200 mA limit |
| **5V rail** | ~35 mA | ✅ Safe (200 mA available) |
| **Button pull-up** | Digital only, no current draw | ✅ Safe |

---

## **How It Works**

1. **Button press detection**: Uses debounce logic (20 ms delay + double-check) to avoid false triggers.
2. **Counter increment**: Each valid button press increments `counter` by 1.
3. **Wrap-around**: When counter exceeds 9, it resets to 0.
4. **Display update**: The `displayDigit()` function maps the counter value (0–9) to 7-segment patterns using standard digit encoding.

Your circuit is ready to use! 🎉
